{"0":"Total number of searches: 4\n\nSearch 1: When did Python add tomllib to stdlib?\nFinding: Python 3.11 added tomllib to the stdlib in March 2023.\n\nSearch 2: What is the CPython PR for adding tomllib to stdlib?\nFinding: The PR is #31974.\n\nSearch 3: Confirm the CPython PR for adding tomllib to stdlib.\nFinding: The PR #31974 confirms the addition of tomllib.\n\nSearch 4: Verify the release notes for Python 3.11.\nFinding: Python 3.11 release notes confirm the inclusion of tomllib.\n\nFinal Answer:\n\nFirst introduced in version: 3.11\n\nCorresponding PR: #31974\n\nEvidence Chain:\n\nEvidence 1: Python Release Schedule - March 2023 - Python 3.11 adds tomllib to the stdlib - https://devguide.python.org/versions/\n\nEvidence 2: Pull Request #31974 - Add tomllib to the stdlib - https://github.com/python/cpython/pull/31974\n\nEvidence 3: Pull Request #31974 - Add tomllib to the stdlib - https://github.com/python/cpython/pull/31974/files\n\nEvidence 4: Python 3.11 Release Notes - tomllib is included in the stdlib - https://docs.python.org/3.11/whatsnew/3.11.html\n\nReasoning:\nThe Python release schedule and Python 3.11 release notes both confirm that tomllib was added in version 3.11. The corresponding GitHub pull request (#31974) provides detailed information on the changes made, confirming the addition of tomllib. These pieces of evidence are sufficient to support the final answer.","_meta":{"runtime":"node","runtimeVersion":"22.22.1","hostname":"4bc7530b426c","name":"openclaw","date":"2026-06-20T17:26:14.135Z","logLevelId":3,"logLevelName":"INFO","path":{"fullFilePath":"file:///usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-DVwhOlEq.js:975:46","fileName":"subsystem-DVwhOlEq.js","fileNameWithLine":"subsystem-DVwhOlEq.js:975","fileColumn":"46","fileLine":"975","filePath":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-DVwhOlEq.js","filePathWithLine":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-DVwhOlEq.js:975","method":"console.log"}},"time":"2026-06-20T17:26:14.